ng archival digitisation, artistic appropriation, and academic reinterpretation of film material that demand scholarly attention. Exploring Past Images in a Digital Age: Reinventing the Archive aims to fill this demand with a thought-provoking collection of original articles contributed by renowned scholars, archivists, and artists. It urges the reader to "forget" standard ways of thinking about film archives and come to grips with the challenges of analysing and recontextualising an area in transit from the analogue to the digital. The book not only throws light on unexplored issues related to film archives but also introduces unconventional approaches and alternative sources for scholarly research and a vast range of artistic possibilities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArts. 0aFilm archives. 0aMotion picture film collections. 4aArt and Material Culture. 4aFilm Studies. 4aFilm, Media, and Communication. 4aMedia Studies. 7aART / History / General.2bisacsh  aFilm Archive, Film History and Historiography, Digital Archiving, Digital Humanities, Memory.1 aBerensel, Ege, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChristie, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElsaesser, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErdogan, Nezih, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErdogan, Nezih, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aIleri, Nurçin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKamp, Claudy Op den, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKayaalp, Ebru, econtributor.4ctb4https://